Planned Changes to Improve Safety

As part of updating the 2004 Risk Management Program, a PHA was performed in 2009 for the chlorination system. Based on the 2009 PHA, a few equipment and procedural changes were recommended. All the above recommendations have been evaluated and implemented by the LADWP, including the installation and operation of a dry media chlorine mini-scrubber. Additionally, four recommendations to further improve chlorine safety were identified in March 2014, when the PHA was performed for the facility (without the main chlorine dry scrubber and withdrawal of only gaseous chlorine from the ton containers). The main chlorine dry media scrubber is currently under installation at the chlorination station and an updated RMP will be submitted after the main chlorine dry scrubber starts normal operation. Based on the 2014 seismic assessment, two recommendations were made to improve chlorine safety. It is expected that all the recommendations will be evaluated by December 2014 and implemented by June 2015.  The implementation of these recommendations will further improve the safety of the chlorine system.
